<page>
    <topic>Building Your First Web Application</topic>
    <description>A step-by-step guide to building your first web application using Alpha Anywhere's Flying Start Genie.</description>
    <groups>
        <group>
            <title>Prerequisites</title>
            <sections>
                <section>
                    <description>
                        <p>*[STOP]*</p>
                        <p>This tutorial assumes you have already completed [Setting Up a Workspace] to create a blank workspace with a connection string to the Northwind database.</p>
                        <p>Have you completed [Setting Up a Workspace]? If your answer to this question is no, please follow the [Setting Up a Workspace] tutorial before starting this tutorial.</p>
                    </description>
                </section>
            </sections>
        </group>
        <group>
            <title>Part 1 - Flying Start Genie</title>
            <sections>
                <section>
                    <description>
                        <p>The Flying Start Genie is a tool that can help you to build a web application quickly.</p>
                    </description>
                </section>
                <section>
                    <steps>
                        <step>
                            <description>From the *[ui:Web Projects Control panel]*, click *[ui:[FileAdd] Add File]*.</description>
                            <figure>
                                <title></title>
                                <link></link>
                            </figure>
                        </step>
                        <step>
                            <description>Select *[ui:Flying Start Genie]* and click *[ui:OK]*.</description>
                            <figure>
                                <title></title>
                                <link>images/flyingStartGenie1.png</link>
                            </figure>
                        </step>
                        <step>
                            <description>On the *[ui:Connect to Database]* tab, set the connection string. Select *[ui:SQL Database]* and click the *[ui:Define Connection String]* to open the Connection String dialog.</description>
                            <figure>
                                <title></title>
                                <link>images/flyingStartGenie2.png</link>
                            </figure>
                        </step>
                        <step>
                            <description>
                                <p>Select *[ui:Use a named connection string]*. Click the *[ui:Select...]* button and select the *[Northwind]* connection string. The Flying Start Genie requires a named connection string. If you do not have a named connection string for the Northwind database, follow Lesson 2 in in [Setting Up a Workspace] to create a named Northwind connection string.</p>
                                <p></p>
                            </description>
                            <figure>
                                <title></title>
                                <link>images/flyingStartGenie3.png</link>
                            </figure>
                        </step>
                        <step>
                            <description>Click *[ui:OK]* to set the connection string. Click *[ui:Next >]* to move to the next step in the Flying Start Genie.</description>
                            <figure>
                                <title></title>
                                <link>images/flyingStartGenie4.png</link>
                            </figure>
                        </step>
                        <step>
                            <description></description>
                            <figure>
                                <title></title>
                                <link></link>
                            </figure>
                        </step>
                        <step>
                            <description></description>
                            <figure>
                                <title></title>
                                <link></link>
                            </figure>
                        </step>
                    </steps>
                </section>
            </sections>
        </group>
    </groups>
    <links>
        <link href="Setting Up a New Workspace">Setting Up a Workspace</link>
    </links>
</page>